Czech Shares Reverse Earlier Declines as NWR, Komercni Advance

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-22T08:13:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/czech-shares-drop-for-third-day-as-erste-telefonica-retreat.html
The Czech Republic’s equity index
reversed earlier losses as New World Resources Plc,  Komercni
Banka AS (KOMB)  and Telefonica Czech Republic AS gained.  The PX gauge of 14 companies rose 0.4 percent to 992.2 as
of 10:05 a.m. in  Prague  after earlier retreating as much as 0.7
percent. NWR, the country’s biggest producer of coking coal,
added 1.6 percent to 161 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  